page.title: 01General
page.content: Our 4X3 km square consists of parts of Rotherhithe Millwall,The Isle of dogs,Deptford and Greenwich areas are given over to the housing apart from a section containing Greenwich Park .The other areas are largly docks and wharfs associated with the river T}hames.The area is rich in history having been a center of British ship building for centuries.Deptford and Greenwich especially have a rich and varied history. The latter area is one of Londons most popular tourist attractions.In recent times much of the traditional work in and around the docks has disappeared and unemployment in the area is high.The area is very rich and varied in peoples and culture Afro-Carribean and Vietnamese forming two large communities in the area.
